From 2288a29abb2fb334d447ca936844c55dbe8fa25d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sebastian Reichel <sebastian.reichel@collabora.com>
Date: Thu, 31 Jul 2025 17:18:36 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 008/142] [MERGED] accel/rocket: Add missing client-id to
 drm_sched_job_init

In 2956554823ce ("drm/sched: Store the drm client_id in drm_sched_fence")
the drm_sched_job_init() function gained an extra parameter containing
the DRM client ID. Add this to rocket to fix the compiler error.

Signed-off-by: Sebastian Reichel <sebastian.reichel@collabora.com>
---
 drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c b/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c
index 378201603cc39..5d4afd6923062 100644
--- a/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c
+++ b/drivers/accel/rocket/rocket_job.c
@@ -552,7 +552,7 @@ static int rocket_ioctl_submit_job(struct drm_device *dev, struct drm_file *file
 
 	ret = drm_sched_job_init(&rjob->base,
 				 &file_priv->sched_entity,
-				 1, NULL);
+				 1, NULL, file->client_id);
 	if (ret)
 		goto out_put_job;
 
